@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

<div class="text-center">

    <section class="mb-5" id="Hero">
        <div class="row align-items-center g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold"> 
                    About <span style="color: steelblue">Loch and Löyly</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="text-start fs-5">
                    We connect Scotland’s love for wild water with the Nordic art of heat. 
                    Loch and Löyly helps you discover authentic sauna experiences and honest reviews, 
                    so you can relax, recover, and reconnect with nature.
                </p>
                <div class="d-flex gap-2">
                    <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="SaunaFinder" class="btn btn-primary">
                        Find a Sauna
                    </a>
                    <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Reviews" class="btn btn-outline-dark">
                        Read Reviews
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5">
                <div class="rounded-4 border"> 
                    <img src="/Images/generatedSauna.png" alt="heroSauna" class="w-100 h-60 object-fit-cover" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5" id="saunaHistory">
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h2 class="text-start"> 
                    History & Origins of Saunas
                </h2>
                <p class="text-start"> 
                    The sauna tradition is over two millennia old, with deep roots in Finland and across the Nordic region. The word löyly describes the spirit of the steam released when water meets hot stones — the essence of sauna.
                </p>
                <p class="text-start">
                    From rustic smoke saunas (savusauna) to modern wood-fired and electric rooms, the ritual has always been about warmth, community, and restoration.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="p-4 bg-light rounded-4 h-100">
                    <p class="text-start fw-bold">
                        <span style="color: steelblue">
                            QUICK FACTS
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-0 text-start">
                        <li>Ancient Nordic practice dating back 2,000+ years</li>
                        <li>Traditional types: smoke sauna, wood-fired, electric</li>
                        <li>Core ritual: heat, löyly (steam), cool, rest — repeat</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5" id="scottishSaunas">
        <h2 class="text-start">
            From Lochs to Löyly: Saunas in Scotland
        </h2>
        <p class="text-start">
            Contrast therapy - alternating head and cold - is growing across the UK. In Scotland, wild swims and cold dips pair naturally with the calming head of a sauna. We curate locations that celabrate this connection, from costal pop-ups to permanent loch-side spots
        </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5" id="healthBenefits">
        <h2 class="text-start">
            Health & Wellbeing Benefits
        </h2>
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-4"> 
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-heart-pulse" style="color: steelblue"></i> Improved Circulation
                    </h3>
                    <p> Heat promotes vasodilation, supporting blood flow and cardiovascular conditioning.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-water" style="color: steelblue"></i> Recovery & Relaxation
                    </h3>
                    <p> Eases muscle tension after training and supports stress reduction and sleep quality.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-brightness-alt-high" style="color: steelblue"></i> Mood and Mental Clarity
                    </h3>
                    <p> Many people report calmer moods and mental clarity following heat–cool cycles.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-droplet-half" style="color: steelblue"></i> Skin Cleansing
                    </h3>
                    <p>Sweating helps cleanse pores; regular sessions can enhance that post-sauna glow.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-shield-check" style="color: steelblue"></i> Immune Support
                    </h3>
                    <p>Heat exposure may stimulate beneficial responses (e.g., heat-shock proteins).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="p-4">
                    <h3 class="h5 mb-0">
                        <i class="bi bi-people" style="color: steelblue"></i> Community & Connection
                    </h3>
                    <p>Sauna is social — a ritual that brings people together in a mindful, phone-free space.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section >
    <section class="mb-5 text-center">
        <h2> Ready for your next sauna session?</h2>       
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="SaunaFinder" class="btn btn-primary">
            Find a Sauna
        </a>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="FAQ" class="btn btn-outline-dark">
            FAQs
        </a>


    </section>

</div>
